<text evidence="1">Negatively autoregulated.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="domain">
<text evidence="8">Consists of two structural and functional domains: an N-terminal DNA-binding domain, approximately the first 60 residues, and a larger C-terminal domain, approximately 280 residues, which imparts the function of corepressor binding and oligomerization.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="miscellaneous">
<text>The corepressors hypoxanthine and guanine bind cooperatively to single PurR sites in each subunit of the dimer, inducing a conformational change which increases the affinity of PurR for its DNA operator sites.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="similarity">
<text>Contains 1 HTH lacI-type DNA-binding domain.</text>
</comment>
